The Fatu Hiva monarch (Pomarea whitneyi) is a large flycatcher in the family Monarchidae. It is endemic to Fatu Hiva in the Marquesas Islands, French Polynesia.  It lives in the native dense forest at elevations up to 2300 feet.  Adults are a glossy purplish-black with plush-like feathers on their foreheads and grow to around 7 Â½ inches.